{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"weak","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:Qoobjc(pl)MLNMapSnapshotterDelegate","text":"id<MLNMapSnapshotterDelegate>","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"delegate","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The delegate is responsible for responding to significant changes during the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"snapshotting process, such as the style loading. Implement a delegate to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"customize the style that is depicted by the snapshot."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You set the delegate after initializing the snapshotter but before receiving"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the snapshot, typically before starting the snapshot. The snapshotter keeps a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"weak reference to its delegate, so you must keep a strong reference to it to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ensure that your style customizations apply."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"title":"delegate","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"delegate"}],"fragments":[{"text":"delegate","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"property","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNMapSnapshotter(py)delegate","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor"